file_contents["CIS-B1-PAB_Preliminary_Architecture_Blueprint.md"] = """# Preliminary Architecture Blueprint\n\n**Document ID:** CIS-B1-PAB\n**CIS Layer:** PLLC\n**Centauri Phase:** Centauri-5\n**TRL Target:** 2–3\n**Grid Slot:** M-010\n**PRECISELIENS Node:** Mirror-0\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\nDefine the initial system architecture, including functional blocks, data flows, interfaces, and constraints. Establish the structural foundation for all prototypes.\n\n## 2. Inputs\n- Umbrella Integration Draft\n- Feasibility Envelope Model\n- Mission constraints\n- Early performance envelope\n\n## 3. Outputs\n- System block diagram\n- Data flow diagrams\n- Interface definitions\n- Architectural assumptions list\n\n## 4. Method\n1. Identify core system functions\n2. Group functions into architectural blocks\n3. Define data and control flows\n4. Establish interface boundaries\n5. Validate against mission constraints\n\n## 5. Mission Integration\n- Identifies which mission systems the architecture must interface with\n- Establishes early comms, power, and data assumptions\n- Ensures compatibility with Artemis/Gateway infrastructure\n\n## 6. TRL & SBIR Mapping\n- TRL: 2–3\n- SBIR: Pre-Phase I → Phase I transition\n\n## 7. Risks & Mitigations\n- **Risk:** Architecture diverges from mission constraints\n  **Mitigation:** Early mission integration reviews\n- **Risk:** Overcomplexity\n  **Mitigation:** Enforce minimal viable architecture\n\n## 8. Change Log\n- 2026-05-17 — Architecture baseline created\n"""
file_contents["CIS-B2-MBL_Mirror_Base_Lattice_Map.md"] = """# Mirror/Base Lattice Map\n\n**Document ID:** CIS-B2-MBL\n**CIS Layer:** PLLC\n**Centauri Phase:** Centauri-6\n**TRL Target:** 2–3\n**Grid Slot:** M-011\n**PRECISELIENS Node:** Mirror-1\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\nMap architectural components into the PLLC Mirror/Base lattice, defining stable logic, core services, and deterministic behaviors.\n\n## 2. Inputs\n- Architecture Blueprint\n- Umbrella lineage\n- Mission constraints\n\n## 3. Outputs\n- Mirror/Base lattice diagram\n- Component placement rationale\n- Stability classification\n- Dependency mapping\n\n## 4. Method\n1. Identify stable vs. dynamic components\n2. Assign stable components to Mirror nodes\n3. Assign dynamic or reactive components to Base nodes\n4. Validate lattice coherence\n\n## 5. Mission Integration\n- Ensures deterministic behavior for mission-critical functions\n- Establishes which components require redundancy\n- Supports mission safety analysis\n\n## 6. TRL & SBIR Mapping\n- TRL: 2–3\n- SBIR: Pre-Phase I → Phase I\n\n## 7. Risks & Mitigations\n- **Risk:** Misclassification of stability\n  **Mitigation:** Stress-test assumptions\n- **Risk:** Lattice imbalance\n  **Mitigation:** Redistribute load across nodes\n\n## 8. Change Log\n- 2026-05-17 — Lattice mapping completed\n"""
file_contents["CIS-B3-A0R_Prototype_Alpha0_Report.md"] = """# Prototype Alpha-0 Report\n\n**Document ID:** CIS-B3-A0R\n**CIS Layer:** PLLC\n**Centauri Phase:** Centauri-7\n**TRL Target:** 2–3\n**Grid Slot:** M-012\n**PRECISELIENS Node:** Mirror-2\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\nDocument the first minimal functional prototype demonstrating the core mechanism under controlled conditions.\n\n## 2. Inputs\n- Architecture Blueprint\n- Lattice Map\n- Feasibility Envelope\n\n## 3. Outputs\n- Alpha-0 design description\n- Implementation notes\n- Initial performance observations\n- Prototype limitations list\n\n## 4. Method\n1. Implement minimal viable architecture\n2. Conduct basic functional tests\n3. Compare results to feasibility bounds\n4. Document deviations and anomalies\n\n## 5. Mission Integration\n- Identifies early mission functions touched by the prototype\n- Highlights interface assumptions requiring validation\n- Establishes early performance expectations\n\n## 6. TRL & SBIR Mapping\n- TRL: 2–3\n- SBIR: Pre-Phase I → Phase I candidate\n\n## 7. Risks & Mitigations\n- **Risk:** Prototype overfits lab conditions\n  **Mitigation:** Document environmental assumptions\n- **Risk:** Architecture drift\n  **Mitigation:** Trace each component back to PAB\n\n## 8. Change Log\n- 2026-05-17 — Alpha-0 baseline documented\n"""
file_contents["CIS-B4-RFMA_Risk_Failure_Mode_Atlas.md"] = """# Risk & Failure Mode Atlas\n\n**Document ID:** CIS-B4-RFMA\n**CIS Layer:** PLLC\n**Centauri Phase:** Centauri-8\n**TRL Target:** 3\n**Grid Slot:** M-013\n**PRECISELIENS Node:** Mirror-3\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\nIdentify, classify, and analyze risks and failure modes across the system, including lunar environmental stressors.\n\n## 2. Inputs\n- Alpha-0 Report\n- Architecture Blueprint\n- Mission constraints\n- Environmental data\n\n## 3. Outputs\n- Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA)\n- Risk matrix\n- Environmental stressor map\n- Mitigation strategies\n\n## 4. Method\n1. Enumerate components and interfaces\n2. Identify failure modes\n3. Assess severity, likelihood, detectability\n4. Map environmental stressors\n5. Define mitigations\n\n## 5. Mission Integration\n- Identifies mission-critical vulnerabilities\n- Supports safety and redundancy planning\n- Informs Phase I test design\n\n## 6. TRL & SBIR Mapping\n- TRL: 3\n- SBIR: Phase I preparation\n\n## 7. Risks & Mitigations\n- **Risk:** Undiscovered failure modes\n  **Mitigation:** Cross-discipline review\n- **Risk:** Underestimated environmental effects\n  **Mitigation:** Conservative modeling\n\n## 8. Change Log\n- 2026-05-17 — RFMA baseline created\n"""
